## Code Style & Conventions

### Component Structure

- Use `"use client"` directive for client components (interactive components, hooks, state)
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Export default for page components
- Use named exports for reusable components
- Keep components focused and single-responsibility

### File Naming

- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `HeroSection.tsx`, `PodcastSection.tsx`)
- Pages: lowercase (e.g., `page.tsx`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `utils.ts`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (e.g., `use-media-query.ts`)

### Component Patterns

```typescript
// Client Component Example
"use client";
import { useState } from "react";
import Image from "next/image";
import Link from "next/link";
import { Container } from "@/components/responsive";
import { gradientVariants } from "@/lib/utils";

export default function ComponentName() {
  const [state, setState] = useState(false);

  return (
    <section className="relative w-full py-8 md:py-12">
      <Container>{/* Component content */}</Container>
    </section>
  );
}
```

### Styling Guidelines

#### Tailwind CSS

- Use Tailwind utility classes for styling
- Prefer composition over custom CSS
- Use responsive breakpoints: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Dark mode: Always use `dark:` prefix for dark mode styles
- Use `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes

#### Common Patterns

- **Gradients**: Use `gradientVariants` from `@/lib/utils` for consistent gradients
  - `gradientVariants.heroOverlay` - Hero section gradient
  - `gradientVariants.contentOverlay` - Content overlay gradients
  - `gradientVariants.bottomTransition` - Bottom gradient transitions
  - `gradientVariants.textOverlay` - Text overlay gradients
- **Containers**: Use `Container` component from `@/components/responsive`
- **Spacing**: Use Tailwind spacing scale (mb-4, p-6, gap-4, etc.)
- **Colors**: Use semantic color names (text-gray-700, bg-white, etc.)
- **Green accent**: Use `bg-green-600` for primary actions (as seen in tabs)

#### Image Handling

- Always use Next.js `Image` component with:
  - `fill` prop for responsive images in containers
  - `priority` for above-the-fold images
  - Appropriate `sizes` attribute for responsive images
  - `object-cover` to fill container (most common)
  - `object-contain` when full image must be visible
  - `object-center` for centering focus
  - Always provide descriptive `alt` text

```typescript
<Image
  src="/assets/images/thumb/thumb-1400x778.jpg"
  alt="Descriptive alt text"
  fill
  className="object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105"
  priority
  sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, (max-width: 1200px) 90vw, 1200px"
/>
```

